meta {
  name: Logout Resets Turns Only
  type: http
  seq: 6
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/webhooks/clerk
  body: json
  auth: none
}

body:json {
  {
    "type": "session.ended",
    "data": {
      "user_id": "{{test_user_id}}"
    }
  }
}

docs {
  ## Sequence
  1. Accumulate turns for `{{test_user_id}}` by sending several chat messages.
  2. Also accumulate some tool_calls and sessions so they are non-zero.
  3. POST this Clerk `session.ended` webhook to `{{base_url}}/webhooks/clerk`.
  4. Send a chat message — verify guard passes (turns reset to 0 so turns breach won't fire).
  5. Confirm sessions and tool_calls are unchanged (not reset by logout).

  ## Expected Effect After Webhook
  - `turns` → 0
  - `sessions.count` → unchanged
  - `toolCalls.count` → unchanged

  ## Notes
  - This endpoint is public (`auth.public_paths` includes `/webhooks/clerk`)
  - In production the request is verified via Svix HMAC signature — set `CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET`
  - For local testing with the dev bypass, the webhook verification will still require a valid
    signature or you can temporarily stub it out
  - NestJS server must be running on port 3333: `pnpm nx serve api`
}
